            "body": "<p>Well reading the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/Character.html#isLowerCase%28char%29\" rel=\"nofollow\">docs<\/a> this tells me that it checks if it is lower case it <code>returns true else returns false<\/code> <\/p>\n\n<p>The code you have i.e <code>a &lt;= myChar &amp;&amp; 'z'&gt;= myChar<\/code> is evaluating to the same thing <code>IF IT WAS ONLY ASCII<\/code> given that:<\/p>\n\n<p>In <code>ascii<\/code> <code>a = 97<\/code> and <code>z= 122<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>The <code>isLower<\/code> function also returns lowercase unicode. <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 25750147,
            "question_id": 25750026,
            "last_edit_date": 1410290160
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/53ee9941b3fefef67175daf212e62d41?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
